		<!-- message -->
		<div>Skeleton archers look exactly like a skeleton with a bow. At level 1, they are basically useless, and last a very short period of time. Level 2 is somewhat useful, although still not worth the aa's. However, level 3 is actually pretty nice. The archers stay up for 90 seconds or a minute, I can't remember and can add considerable damage. Although they have a reuse time of 30 minutes, they can be very good for critical situations because they not only have an instant cast time, but cost 0 mana, obviously. It's a way to increase your damage on a big mob considerably, especially if you WTD at the same time, you can have 5 pets running, all doing damage.<br />
<br />
    Tenebrous mountains is a pretty good kiting spot. The wolves and soldiers are a bit higher level, but you can start with the grimling caves at about level 32-33. The grimlings have about 700-1000 hp, and the geomancers are nasty casters, but die quickly. Bring some bags, you'll have some acrylia.<br />
    In Ldon's i don't even keep a dot memmed(except lifetap over time) and I just chain nuke, usually grabbing aggro, but thats b/c I'm an aggro whore. This is my setup almost always(in an undead theme)<br />
1-Touch of Mujaki<br />
2-Neurotoxin<br />
3-Destroy Undead(replace with embracing darkness in non undead theme)<br />
4-Shackle of Spirit(replace with (Zevfeer's theft of vitae in an non undead theme)<br />
5-Death Peace<br />
6-Greater Immobilize<br />
7-Mind Wrack<br />
8-Saryrn's Kiss<br />
    <br />
    I never ever ever ever ever twitch unless im doing for instance a hard ldon and the cleric has no crack or needs a break. I twitch occassionally in non-ldon instances and on raids, but its usually after a wipe or at a critical time. It's incredibly inefficient to twitch while the group is killing, the person would save more mana if you just nuked because the mob would die quicker. Mind wrack is a really awesome spell that you get at level 58, it's useful in so many places, and costs virtually no mana after spell casting mastery and mana pres kicks in. You have to keep in mind what your group setup is. If you have a lot of melee's, you'd be best off memming the group atk tap. If you have a druid healer who doesn't have a group heal, keep zevfeer's up. You have to be able to adjust based on your group, and the situation, thats what makes a necro a good group member.<br />
<br />
Hope I've answered ur questions.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
